elog_lib v1.0.1 | Mar 07 2026:

-- SIEM Output Modules --
  [New] CEF output module with ArcSight Common Event Format (v0) support
  [New] CEF severity mapping (debug=1, info=3, warn=5, error=7, critical=10)
  [New] CEF header and extension escaping (pipe, backslash, equals, newline)
  [New] Syslog UDP output module with RFC 5424 and RFC 3164 format support
  [New] Fire-and-forget UDP delivery via /dev/udp with nc fallback
  [New] Syslog severity mapping and PRI calculation (facility * 8 + severity)
  [New] Configurable syslog payload format (classic, json, cef)
  [New] Event context staging for SIEM handler access to structured event data
  [New] GELF output module with Graylog Extended Log Format 1.1 support
  [New] GELF timestamp conversion to Unix epoch via _elog_ts_epoch()
  [New] GELF short_message truncation at 256 chars with full_message for overflow
  [New] GELF transport selection: UDP (reusing _elog_udp_send) or HTTP
  [New] GELF custom fields with underscore prefix (_app, _pid, _event_type, _tag)
  [New] ELK JSON output module with ECS (Elastic Common Schema) field alignment
  [New] ECS category mapping from elog taxonomy (intrusion_detection, configuration,
      network, notification, process)
  [New] ECS event.type mapping (denied, allowed, change, start, end, error, info)
  [New] HTTP delivery infrastructure with curl/wget auto-detection and fallback
  [New] Fire-and-forget HTTP POST via background subshell (_elog_http_send)
  [New] 57 new tests across CEF, syslog UDP, GELF, and ELK test suites

-- Bug Fixes --
  [Fix] Trailing newline from here-string stripped in CEF, GELF, and ELK extras parsing
  [Fix] UDP detection probe in elog_init() gated by elog_output_enabled
      instead of _elog_output_find (probe only fires when module is enabled)
  [Fix] CEF signatureId field header-escaped for defensive correctness
